/**
 * @param {number[]} nums
 * @param {number} k
 * @return {number}
 */
var maximumLength = function(tides, k) {
    const size = tides.length;
    const depths = Array.from({ length: size }, () => Array(k + 1).fill(1));
    let max_depth = 1;
    const max_depths = Array(k + 1).fill(-1);
    const tide_to_depths_map = Array.from({ length: k + 1 }, () => ({}));

    for (let i = 0; i < size; i++) {
        for (let j = 0; j <= k; j++) {
            for (let l = 0; l < j; l++) {
                depths[i][j] = Math.max(depths[i][j], 1 + max_depths[l]);
            }

            if (tide_to_depths_map[j][tides[i]] !== undefined) {
                depths[i][j] = Math.max(depths[i][j], 1 + tide_to_depths_map[j][tides[i]]);
            }

            max_depth = Math.max(max_depth, depths[i][j]);
        }

        for (let j = 0; j <= k; j++) {
            max_depths[j] = Math.max(max_depths[j], depths[i][j]);
            tide_to_depths_map[j][tides[i]] = Math.max(tide_to_depths_map[j][tides[i]] || 0, depths[i][j]);
        }
    }
